    <h2>Lebanese Ice Cream</h2>
    <p>
      Booza is the predecessor to modern ice cream the way we are familiar with it today. Born five hundred or so years
      ago in the region of the Mediterranean, it is a favorite in most Arab countries. Stretchy and chewy with a
      traditional flavor of mastic and milk cream it is a glorious soft serve ice cream. Vendors used to use insulated
      cans with big corks on the top that served as mobile ice cream shops.
    </p>
