    <p>
      Gelato is a popular frozen dessert of Italian origin. Generally made with a base of 3.25% milk and sugar, gelato
      can contain up to 70% less air and more flavouring than other kinds of frozen desserts. It's this quality that
      gives gelato its density and richness that distinguishes it from other ice creams.
