    <h2>Japanese Mochi</h2>
    <p>
      Mochi is a chewy Japanese rice cake made of mochigome, a short-grain japonica glutinous rice. The rice is pounded
      into paste and molded, and is traditionally made in a ceremony called mochitsuki. While it’s enjoyed year-round,
      it’s especially eaten around Japanese New Year as a part of the festivities. Delicous and cute, mochi also has a
      dark side - each year, authorities issue public warnings in the run-up to the new year advising that the very
      young and elderly should only eat mochi cut down to smaller little chunks. At the turn of 2014 to 2015, nine
      people died from not being able to properly swallow their mochi.
    </p>
